'''Ahmed Best''' (born [[August 19]], [[1973]])<ref name="Year By Year" /> is an actor who portrayed [[Jar Jar Binks]] in all three films of the [[prequel trilogy]] and [[Jedi Master]] [[Kelleran Beq]] in the game show ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Temple Challenge]]'' and in the television series [[Star Wars: The Mandalorian|''The Mandalorian'']].

==Biography==
===Roles===
[[File:KelleranBeq.png|thumb|left|250px|Best in his role as Kelleran Beq]]
Besides his role as [[Jar Jar Binks]] in the [[prequel trilogy]], Best has also appeared as an extra in the role of [[Outlander Club]] patron [[Achk Med-Beq]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="SW Show May 2020">{{StarWarsShow|fKdMtEiHGnM|Ahmed Best and Mary Holland Talk Jedi Temple Challenge, And We Celebrate The Empire Strikes Back!|sw_url=video/ahmed-best-and-mary-holland-talk-jedi-temple-challenge-and-we-celebrate-the-empire-strikes-back}}</ref> He also hosted the behind-the-scenes web series ''[[on location]]'' for [[StarWars.com]] during the film's production.<ref name="Home">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/onloc|text=''on location'' home page}}</ref> He has had voice roles in ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' and various ''Star Wars'' video games, mostly reprising his role as Jar Jar Binks, but occasionally as other characters.<ref name="Gungan Attack">{{TCW|Gungan Attack}}</ref>

On [[December 3]], [[2019]], Best was announced as the host of the game show ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Temple Challenge]]''. On [[May 27]], [[2020]], it was announced that Best would be playing the role of [[Jedi Master]] [[Kelleran Beq]], and that the show would be released on YouTube rather than [[Disney+]], as was originally announced.<ref name="Jedi Temple Challenge">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-jedi-temple-challenge-premiere|text=Updated: ''Star Wars: Jedi Temple Challenge'' to Debut June 10 on ''Star Wars'' Kids}}</ref> ''Jedi Temple Challenge'' premiered on [[June 10]], 2020.<ref name="Step Inside">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-jedi-temple-challenge-interviews|text=Step Inside ''Star Wars: Jedi Temple Challenge''}}</ref> Ahmed revisited the role when he played Kelleran Beq again in [[Star Wars: The Mandalorian|''The Mandalorian'']]: "[[Chapter 20: The Foundling]]" which premiered on [[March 22]], [[2023]].<ref name="Chapter 20" />

Best also voiced an alternate version of Binks known as "Darth Jar Jar" in the non-[[Canon]] animated series ''[[LEGO Star Wars: Rebuild the Galaxy]]'', which premiered on [[Disney+]] on [[September 13]], [[2024]].<ref name="Rebuild">{{SW|url=news/lego-star-wars-rebuild-the-galaxy|text=Get Ready for Darth Jar Jar, TIE-Wings, and More in ''LEGO Star Wars: Rebuild the Galaxy''}}</ref> Best later confirmed during [[Celebration Japan (2025)|Celebration Japan]] on [[April 19]], [[2025]] that he would be reprising his role as "Darth Jar Jar" in the second season ''[[LEGO Star Wars: Rebuild the Galaxy - Pieces of the Past]]'', which is expected to be released on Disney+ on September 19.<ref name="Pieces of the Past">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-celebration-2025-lego-star-wars-rebuild-the-galaxy-pieces-of-the-past|text=''LEGO Star Wars: Rebuild the Galaxy: Pieces of the Past'' Will Feature LEGO BrickHeadz Ahsoka and&hellip; Jaxxon?!}}</ref>

===Fan reception===
Ahmed Best addressed the mixed and sometimes hostile fan reaction to Jar Jar Binks when interviewed in [[Star Wars Insider 56|''Star Wars Insider'' 56]]. In 2018, because Jar Jar was so disliked, Best announced that he had previously considered suicide. This provoked an outpouring of support from fans.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-44708983|text=Star Wars: Jar Jar Binks actor Ahmed Best considered suicide|date=2018-07-04|work=[[Wikipedia:BBC News|BBC News]]|archivedate=20180728073340}}</ref><ref name="Hollywood Reporter 3 July 2018">{{WebCite|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jar-jar-binks-actor-ahmed-best-considered-suicide-star-wars-backlash-1124848|text=Jar Jar Binks Actor Says He Considered Suicide After 'Star Wars' Backlash|author=Ryan Parker|date=2018-07-03|work=[[Wikipedia:The Hollywood Reporter|''The Hollywood Reporter'']]|archivedate=20200511091211}}</ref>

During an interview with [[Lucasfilm]] employee and ''[[This Week! in Star Wars]]'' host [[Kristin Baver]] in June 2020, Best expressed a "pleasant surprise" at his casting call to play Jedi Master Kelleran Beq. He described the representation of Master Beq as a "person of color" and leader of a Jedi Temple as "breaking new ground" in the ''Star Wars'' universe and creating a "brand new world of possibilities."<ref name="Step Inside" />

